  "title": "instantsearch.js@3.2.0:2 Uncaught EvalError: Refused to evaluate a string as JavaScript",
  "body": "Hi, I've implemented algolia on my website.\r\n\r\nI imported the following scripts:\r\n```\r\n<script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/algoliasearch@3.32.1/dist/algoliasearchLite.js\" integrity=\"sha256-pMaJf0I78weeXGkRMBDO6jSulxC/q3sb0aPdtV2N8n0=\" crossorigin=\"anonymous\"></script>\r\n<script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/instantsearch.js@3.2.0\" integrity=\"sha256-/8usMtTwZ01jujD7KAZctG0UMk2S2NDNirGFVBbBZCM=\" crossorigin=\"anonymous\"></script>\r\n```\r\n\r\nI add the following value to the nginx configuration file:\r\n`add_header \"Content-Security-Policy\" script-src 'unsafe-inline' cdn.jsdelivr.net [...]`\r\n\r\nThe same procedure I did with all the other scripts. I find this error only with algolia\r\n\r\nI get the following error:\r\n`VM10446 instantsearch.js@3.2.0:2 Uncaught EvalError: Refused to evaluate a string as JavaScript because 'unsafe-eval' is not an allowed source of script in the following Content Security Policy directive: \"script-src 'unsafe-inline' .....`\r\n\r\nHow to solve?",
